The Telegraph - Calcutta : International
 Sunday, June 20, 2004 				 Eyes wide shut for just a kiss
																								Singapore, June 19 (AP): Ever wondered why many people close their eyes when they kiss? 																								A Singapore academic said today that smoochers may drop their lids to avoid overloading the senses and  just possibly  to skip the unpleasantness of seeing their lovers blurry from up close. 																								The answer may depend on the way you look at it, associated Prof. Yau Che Ming says in todays Straits Times newspaper. With kissing in action, this induces sensory overload, Yau said. 																								Therefore, closing the eyes is a natural way to reduce the sensory load, he wrote.
